# User Story

The "Product Story"

As a producer, I want to add a photo and a short anecdote about the history of my farm, in order to create an emotional connection with the restaurateur and their customers.

The "Anti-Waste" Alert

As a market gardener, I want to send a "Flash Sale" notification for surplus harvest, so that I can quickly sell my stock at a reduced price instead of throwing it away.

The "Harvest Calendar"

As a farmer, I want to publish my harvest forecasts for the coming month, so that chefs can anticipate their future seasonal menus.

The "Fair Price"

As a livestock farmer, I want to display the breakdown of my price (production cost vs margin), in order to justify the quality of my work to buyers.


Restaurateur Side (Marketing and Transparency)

The Generated "Menu Kit"

As a chef, I want to be able to download QR codes for my suppliers' profiles, so that I can print them on my menus and prove the local origin of my dishes.

The "Discovery Basket"

As a restaurateur, I want to order a "mystery basket" of seasonal samples, so that I can test new products without placing a large order.

The "Zero-Kilometer" Alert

As a manager, I want to receive an alert when a new producer registers within a 10 km radius, so that I can prioritize ultra-local sourcing.


Community Side (Trust)

The "Loyalty Badge"

As an F2R user, I want to see a "Historic Partner" badge on profiles that have been collaborating for more than one year, so that I can identify established and trusted partnerships.
